randoop.operation

Class ArrayCreation

  • Object
    • AbstractOperation
      • ArrayCreation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Operation>, Operation

    public final class ArrayCreation
extends AbstractOperation
implements Operation, Serializable
    ArrayCreation is an Operation representing the construction of a one-dimensional array with a given element type and length. The The ArrayCreation operation requires a list of elements in an initializer. For instance, new int[2] is the ArrayCreation in the initialization
    int[] x = new int[2] { 3, 7 };
    with the initializer list as inputs.

    In terms of the notation used for the Operation class, a creation of an array of elements of type e with length n has a signature [e,...,e] → t, where [e,...,e] is a list of length n, and t is the array type.

    ArrayCreation objects are immutable.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        public String toParseableString()
        Returns a string representation of this Operation, which can be read by static parse method for class. For a class C implementing the Operation interface, this method should return a String s such that parsing the string returns an object equivalent to this object, i.e. C.parse(this.s).equals(this). Creates string of the form TYPE[NUMELEMS] where TYPE is the type of the array, and NUMELEMS is the number of elements. Example: int[3]
